// useDesignSync
// Loads a design's SceneGraph from the API when designId changes, auto-saves changes back, and applies remote WebSocket updates.

Auto-save is debounced at 1000ms. Only versions newer than the last saved sceneVersion trigger a save.
On design switch, any pending save is flushed synchronously for the outgoing design before loading the new one.
Images in the SceneGraph are serialized as base64 strings. Map fields (variables, variableCollections, activeMode) are
serialized as key/value arrays since JSON.stringify cannot handle Maps.

FUNCTION useDesignSync(designId) -> { handleRemoteUpdate }                      EXPORT
  CALLS: api (api), setSceneGraph (designEditorRefs), resetSceneGraph (designEditorRefs),
         getEditorRefs (designEditorRefs), useDesignEditorStore (designEditorStore),
         useSessionStore (sessionStore), SceneGraph (scene-graph), createDefaultNode (scene-graph)
  On designId change: loads the design from the API, deserializes the SceneGraph, initializes the
  editor store from the graph, marks the loaded version as already-saved, and zooms to fit.
  On designId cleanup: flushes any pending debounced save to the outgoing design (fire-and-forget).
  On sceneVersion change: schedules a debounced save if the version is newer than lastSaved.

---

FUNCTION serializeGraph(graph) -> string
  Collects all nodes, variables, variableCollections, activeMode, and images from the graph.
  Encodes image Uint8Arrays as base64. Returns the whole structure as a JSON string.

---

FUNCTION deserializeGraph(json) -> SceneGraph
  Parses the JSON and reconstructs a SceneGraph.
  Each node is merged with createDefaultNode defaults so MCP-created nodes have all required fields.
  Restores Map fields and decodes base64 images back to Uint8Arrays.

---

FUNCTION handleRemoteUpdate(content)
  Receives serialized SceneGraph content from a WebSocket message.
  Deserializes the graph, replaces the current scene graph, and bumps renderVersion and sceneVersion.
  Marks the new version as already-saved so it does not trigger an auto-save.
  Ignores malformed content silently.
